I speak 4 languages: English Japanese Chinese and Taiwanese.  Some people may say Taiwanese is just a dialect from Chinese but it actually has its own characters.  Not a lot of people know this combination because there is rarely any similarity among them.  English and Chinese have similar language structures (Subject + Verb + Object where as in Japanese it is Subject + Object + Verb) but have very different characters.  Japanese borrows a small subset of Chinese and English in the characters but the language structure is very different.  It gets confusing when I have to switch among them.
